  "texts": [
    "However, such simplistic approaches have limitations in handling non-linear and complex data patterns, leading to a high false positive rate and low detection accuracy.",
    "When choosing an approach to detect anomalies, the most crucial factor to consider is the underlying detection method or strategy as shown by the authors in [11].",
    "In this context, using specific metrics to detect anomalies also falls under the category of methods.",
    "This category offers a wide range of options as numerous ideas and concepts from various fields have been adapted for anomaly detection.",
    "Figure 1 illustrates the primary classes of methods.To overcome the limitations and enhance anomaly detection performance, researchers turned to ML-based approaches."
  ]
